.TH ENTERPRISE_SERVER 1 "Enterprise Data Server"
.SH NAME
enterprise_server \- data management server
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B enterprise_server
.SH COMMANDS
.SS Data Commands
.TP
.B ADD
Add new user. Asks for name, age, email, phone.
.TP
.B GET \fIname\fR
Show user details.
.TP
.B LIST
Show all users in table.
.TP
.B UPDATE \fIname\fR
Change user information.
.TP
.B DELETE \fIname\fR
Remove user.
.SS Search Commands
.TP
.B SEARCH \fIterm\fR
Find users by name, email, or phone.
.TP
.B STATS
Show server information.
.SS System Commands
.TP
.B BACKUP
Make data backup.
.TP
.B GENERATE
Create test users.
.TP
.B CLEAR
Delete all users. Must type CONFIRM.
.TP
.B HELP
Show commands.
.TP
.B EXIT
Stop server.
.SH FILES
.TP
.B enterprise_database.dat
User data file.
.TP
.B enterprise_backup.dat
Backup file.
.TP
.B system_log.txt
Activity log.
.SH USAGE
.TP
.B Start server:
./enterprise_server
.TP
.B Add user:
cmd> ADD
.TP
.B Find user:
cmd> GET john
.TP
.B Show all:
cmd> LIST
.TP
.B Search:
cmd> SEARCH company
.TP
.B Stop server:
cmd> EXIT
.SH COMPILE
g++ main.cpp -o enterprise_server -std=c++11
